<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1907/504771.jpg" alt="South African sentiment moves forward" width="600" height="933">“Despite volatile petrol prices and costly utilities, which have placed a strain on essential living costs, South Africans managed to retain a stable outlook in Q1’19 leading to a 2-point increase in consumer confidence.  Against the backdrop of relatively low inflation rates, there has also been an improvement in their perception of their personal finances. However, this is countered by a healthy dose of realism; with more than three quarters of households having cut back on their spending and the economy remaining South Africans' top concern.” - Kerith Botha, Managing Director-Connect, Nielsen South Africa    NOTE sourcing for the SA CCi data is very specific: The Conference Board® Global Consumer Confidence Survey, conducted in collaboration with Nielsen